From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000001 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Danilo Diaz <danilodt@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 14 May 2026 23:00:00 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] meta-balena-raspberrypi: layer.conf: revpi-core-se vfat
 KERNEL_FEATURES:remove

Mirror the existing KERNEL_FEATURES:remove entries for the revpi-connect
family. balenaOS uses ext4 for the root partition; the vfat feature
pulled in by the upstream RPi kernel config is unnecessary on the
revpi-core-se and adds image size.

Reproduces the equivalent change from closed upstream PR #1285,
rebased onto balena-os/balena-raspberrypi @ v6.12.3+rev4.
---
 layers/meta-balena-raspberrypi/conf/layer.conf | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/layers/meta-balena-raspberrypi/conf/layer.conf b/layers/meta-balena-raspberrypi/conf/layer.conf
--- a/layers/meta-balena-raspberrypi/conf/layer.conf
+++ b/layers/meta-balena-raspberrypi/conf/layer.conf
@@ -167,5 +167,6 @@ IWLWIFI_FW_TOCLEAN:raspberrypi0-2w-64 = ""

 KERNEL_FEATURES:remove:revpi-connect-s = "cfg/fs/vfat.scc"
 KERNEL_FEATURES:remove:revpi-connect-4 = "cfg/fs/vfat.scc"
+KERNEL_FEATURES:remove:revpi-core-se = "cfg/fs/vfat.scc"

 VC4DTBO = "vc4-kms-v3d,cma-320"
--
2.43.0

